Class PickCommand

java.lang.Object
  lps.pr2.commands.Command
      lps.pr2.commands.PickCommand
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
public class PickCommand
extends Command

This class implements the PICK <item> command. When this command is executed, an item in the room is picked and stored in the player inventory.

If there isn't any item in the room with this name the command prints a warning message about that the item was not found.

If the player inventory contains an item with the same name, the item cannot be picked and a warning message about this fact is displayed

Method Detail

execute

public void execute()
Executes the command, picking the item identified by its name that lays in the room and storing it in the inventory.

However, if the room does not store any item with this name or the inventory contains an item with the same name, then the action is not executed and a warning message is displayed.
